cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CC

This paper is about the ability of neural networks to capture relational knowledge in language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the limitations of traditional neural network models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper specifically tests two models, which suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the controversy surrounding the ability of neural networks to handle relational structure, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
